# Blog Post Conventions

## Frontmatter Structure

Every post must have YAML frontmatter with these fields:

```yaml
---
title: "[Series Prefix] Title Here"
description: "SEO-friendly description"
date: "YYYY-MM-DD"
doctype: book

series: "Series Name"       # Optional
series_part: N              # Optional

featured_image: /category/images/Logo-Name.png        # Optional
show_featured_image_summary: true                     # Show in list/summary view
show_featured_image_article: true                     # Show in article view
featured_image_position: 50% 35%                      # Optional, CSS position

authors: [Thomas Jungbauer]
type: post
draft: false
categories:
   - Category1
   - Category2
tags: ["tag1", "tag2"]

aliases: [
   "/posts-output/YYYY-MM-DD-slug/",
]
---
```

## Required AsciiDoc Attributes

After frontmatter, include:

```asciidoc
:imagesdir: /category/images/
:icons: font
:toc:
```

## Content Structure

- Use `<!--more-->` to mark the excerpt break
- Headings: `==` for H2, `===` for H3, `====` for H4
- Never use `=` (H1) in content - title comes from frontmatter

## Code Blocks

```asciidoc
[source,yaml]
----
code: here
----
```

Use callouts for explanations:

```asciidoc
[source,yaml]
----
key: value <1>
other: setting <2>
----
<1> Explanation of first callout
<2> Explanation of second callout
```

## Admonitions

Use: `NOTE:`, `TIP:`, `WARNING:`, `IMPORTANT:`, `CAUTION:`

## Links and Images

- Internal links: `link:/category/post-slug/[Link Text]`
- External links: `https://example.com[Link Text^]` (^ opens new tab)
- Images: `image::filename.png?width=720px[Alt text]`

## File Naming

Pattern: `YYYY-MM-DD-Title-With-Dashes.adoc`
